    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>An Inconvenient Woman</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Robert J Christensen letter on David France's May 28 article praises bravery of transsexual Calpernia Sarah Addams in face of murder of Pfc Barry Winchell</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>I admire Calpernia Addams's bravery and hope she yet finds the kind of happiness that Barry Winchell's tragic death cut short. I can never understand why we must force others into our categories. I was struck by Barry's easy acceptance of himself and Calpernia and the readiness with which ''It's O.K.'' came to his lips -- and perhaps contributed to his death.</p>
        <p>Robert J. Christensen</p>
        <p>Eugene, Ore.</p>
      </block>
